Time to get some fiyah in your belly 🔥🔥🔥 The wonderful folks at @theoldpostoffice.space brewing up our Rwanda Rushashi. 
#Repost @theoldpostoffice.space
• • • • •
70% of all work that goes into producing coffee is done by women*, but women* are incredibly unrepresented across the industry.  @girlswhogrindcoffee, who roast the coffee you'll find in our kitchen, exist to change that. 
Our current coffee is from Rwanda, and tastes like candied orange and nectarines. It's grown by the Abakundakawa Rushashi Coffee collective, a cooperative from Gakenke in Northern Rwanda. 📸 @thepaulstringer

🖤 JOIN THE GWGC TEAM⚡

We're on the lookout for an awesome addition to our team at @girlswhogrindcoffee HQ. ⭐Part-time Roastery Assistant⭐ approx 28 hours per week. 
We're looking for a kickass Roastery Assistant. You will ideally have some experience working in specialty coffee or a strong desire to learn about it. We are all about empowering women, so this also needs to be something you believe strongly in. 
Your responsibilities will be, but not limited to, labelling coffee bags, packing coffee, assisting with roasting, general cleaning, setting up the cupping table. **please note** As our Roastery is based on a working farm in Upton Scudamore in Wiltshire (in the middle of nowhere) applicants must be local,  available Monday to Friday and have a car and Drivers Licence. 
Please email hey@girlswhogrindcoffee.com with your CV and a brief paragraph about why you're the right person for the role. 💪🖤
